commit.message:
Don’t use pseudo-types in type checks. (#378)

Emacs 29 is stricter than Emacs 28 and issues warnings when using types
implicitly defined using predicate functions.  Remove type checks where they
don’t pull their weight (e.g. there’s no need to explicitly check that buffers
are live since every function using them will already do so), and convert others
into explicit tests.

verification.payload:
tree a604d62a5eec30c10c21284670e10ea2a15ce4a8
parent d042e28c5bbb407186c8983841e76d109dead471
author Philipp Stephani <phst@google.com> 1681737618 +0200
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1681737618 +0200
